address: Thị trấn Plei Kần, Huyện Ngọc Hồi, Tỉnh Kon Tum
thought:
**My Thought Process: Mapping an Old Address to a New Administrative Unit**

Okay, so the user wants to know the new equivalent of "Thị trấn Plei Kần, Huyện Ngọc Hồi, Tỉnh Kon Tum."  I need to figure this out systematically. First, I identify the old province, "Tỉnh Kon Tum."  Then, I check my province resolutions.  Aha! Resolution 60-NQ/TW states that "Tỉnh Kon Tum" was merged with "Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi." So, my new province is "Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi."

Next, I zero in on "Thị trấn Plei Kần." I need to find its new administrative unit. I search the "Other resolutions" data, looking for any mention of it.  Bingo! Resolution 1677/NQ-UBTVQH15 jumps out at me.  It says "Sắp xếp toàn bộ diện tích tự nhiên, quy mô dân số của thị trấn Plei Kần, xã Đăk Xú và xã Pờ Y thành xã mới có tên gọi là **xã Bờ Y**."  Excellent, "Thị trấn Plei Kần" is now part of "xã Bờ Y."

To confirm, I cross-reference this with my "New wards" data.  I search for "xã Bờ Y" and find a perfect match:  `{"ward_code":"23377","ward_name":"Xã Bờ Y","province_name":"Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi"}`. The province name "Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi" aligns perfectly with what I determined earlier.  That's a strong confirmation.

Since I have a direct match and the province also checks out, my confidence is very high. I'll construct the JSON output using the relevant citation from the resolution (1677/NQ-UBTVQH15).

Let me just double-check for any other related resolutions. I see mentions of "Huyện Ngọc Hồi" and other wards, but they aren't relevant to "Thị trấn Plei Kần," which is my focus. The resolution 1677/NQ-UBTVQH15 gives me the answer: "xã Bờ Y". My JSON output will be straightforward, containing the citation, confidence level, the new province ("Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi"), ward code, and ward name. There is only one candidate found with high confidence.
